BEGIN_PGML

A cylindrical conductor of radius [`r=[$r]`] [`m`] is placed along the z-axis. The current density in the conductor is:

>>[``J = [$N] e^{-(1-\rho/r)} a_z\quad A/m^2``]<<

Find the total current passing through the plane at [`z=0`].

[`I=`] [_____]{"$I"} [`A`]  

END_PGML

